# Placement Preparation Journey 🚀

This repository documents my placement preparation journey from **Day 1** until I secure a full-time role.

The goal of this repository is to maintain consistency, track progress, and create a record of everything I learn throughout the placement season.

## What This Repository Contains

### Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA)

* Daily problem-solving practice
* Topic-wise notes
* LeetCode and coding challenge solutions
* Interview-focused patterns and techniques

### Development Projects

* Full-stack projects
* AI/ML projects
* Web development projects
* Personal and experimental projects

### Core Computer Science

* Object-Oriented Programming
* Operating Systems
* Database Management Systems
* Computer Networks
* System Design fundamentals

### Aptitude & Interview Preparation

* Quantitative aptitude
* Logical reasoning
* Verbal ability
* HR interview preparation
* Behavioral and situational questions

### Placement Resources

* Company-specific preparation
* Online assessments
* Interview experiences
* Resume improvements
* Learning resources and notes

## Why I Started This Repository

Placement preparation can often feel unstructured and difficult to track. This repository serves as a personal log of my journey, helping me:

* Stay accountable
* Maintain consistency
* Measure progress over time
* Document lessons learned
* Build discipline through daily effort

## Progress Tracking

I plan to update this repository regularly with:

* Daily learning logs
* Completed DSA questions
* New projects
* Interview preparation notes
* Placement milestones

## Current Goal

To become a well-rounded software engineer by strengthening my problem-solving, development, and interview skills, and ultimately secure a role at a company where I can learn, grow, and make a meaningful impact.

